  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chimanimani WASH for Sustainable Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to improve access to water for multiple uses for Tubanju and Nyamusundu rural Primary Schools and surrounding communities in Chimanimani districts of Zimbabwe through solar powered and gravity piped water scheme.  A mini-hydro electricity generator will be installed on the gravity scheme to supply the school with electricity primarily for lighting, computer powering as well as charging the phones. In addition, the project will construct six squathole toilet blocks per school with handwashing facilities to cater for teachers, people living with disability and mensural hygiene. School Health and Nutrition Clubs will be formed at each school primarily to influence good sanitation and hygiene practices and snack hygiene within the school. The larger community will benefit when pupils relate to their parents the on learned health and nutrition aspects.</narrative>
  </description>
